<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.883224>
    dc:description "FIGURES 116 – 121. Anarchonirmus albovittatus n. gen. & n. sp. ex Pomatostomus temporalis strepitans: 116, male head, dorsal and ventral view; dorsal sensilla and pts not visible in the material examined. 117, female antenna, ventral view. 118, male genitalia, dorsal view. 119, male mesosome, ventral view. 120, male paramere, dorsal view. 121, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view (anterior dotted line outline pigmented part of subgenital plate, posterior dotted line extent of marginal thickening)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/883224/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.883228>
    dc:description "FIGURES 124 – 129. Osculonirmus limpidus Mey, 1982 a ex Eremophila alpestris utahensis: 124, male head, dorsal and ventral views. 125, female antennae, ventral view. 126, male genitalia, dorsal view. 127, male mesosome, ventral view. 128, male paramere, dorsal view. 129, female subgenital plate and vulval margin, ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/883228/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.883222>
    dc:description "FIGURES 114 – 115. Anarchonirmus albovittatus n. gen. & n. sp. ex Pomatostomus temporalis strepitans: 114, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 115, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views. (dotted lines on sternites outline densely pigmented areas)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/883222/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.883226>
    dc:description "FIGURES 122 – 123. Osculonirmus limpidus Mey, 1982 a ex Eremophila alpestris utahensis: 122, male habitus, dorsal and ventral views. 123, female habitus, dorsal and ventral views." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/883226/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.883171>
    dc:description "FIGURES 25. Dorso-ventral views of coxae I – III, trochanters I – III, and femora I – III, showing terminology of the leg setae used here. Other parts of the thorax removed for clarity. Setae situated marginally are illustrated and named on both dorsal (lefthand) and ventral (right-hand) sides. Terminology for individual seta as used in the text obtained by combining the leg segment (larger font) and the setal name (smaller font). Abbreviations: a 1 – 5, anterior setae 1 – 5; cI – III, coxae I – III; d 1 – 3, dorsal setae 1 – 3; dm 1 – 4, distal marginal setae 1 – 4; fI – III, femur I – III; p 1 – 3, posterior setae 1 – 3; s 1 – 6, sensilla 1 – 6; tI – III, trochanter I – III; v 1 – 4, ventral setae 1 – 4." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/883171/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

